reviews.text: Ordered through GrubHub for delivery. I got the Alejandro burrito with added eggs, but the beans were so plentiful it just tasted like a bean burrito. In the future I would say only use half the amount (yes it was that much!) Guac was good but just a tiny cup for $8, I wouldn‚Äôt order it again, but maybe the portion size is bigger in the restaurant. Salsa was delicious as were the chips. Churro was really good too, came cut in half so was two pieces- good for sharing. Tater tots were yummy. Asked for no ice in the horchata, but they sent it with ice so it was partially melted and there was a ton of ice so didn‚Äôt feel like I got a large at all. My friend said his bean and cheese burrito was really good.

Got to be honest‚Ä¶. I was hesitant‚Ä¶. But their food blew me away starting with the salsa‚Ä¶.. have red and green salsa that was some of the best I‚Äôve had and I‚Äôm a Texan and have had a lot of salsa‚Ä¶.the fajitas were very good as well‚Ä¶. I recommend this place to locals and visitors. Only thing they didn‚Äôt have was fresh brewed tea‚Ä¶.. we stick with water‚Ä¶..boxed tea from fountain is not good from anywhere you get it.

Absolutely DELICIOUS! Honestly probably the best enchiladas I've ever had. Everything was so flavorful. This is a family run business that puts so much heart into their food and the service. Can't recommend it enough!

This place is so unique, the place is small but has big portions and great taste. Our server was German, he was attentive, very nice, and made sure we were liking the food! 10/10 I‚Äôve come here twice already, will come back!

Food wasn‚Äôt great but wasn‚Äôt horrible. Consume for the birria tacos tastes like canned enchilada sauce. $14 for their ‚ÄúLoaded Fries‚Äù is crazy expensive for what you get. Staff was friendly and food came out in a timely manner.
